-- Mexico Stocks: America Movil, Banorte, Banregio Were Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-06-12T20:55:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-12/mexico-stocks-america-movil-banorte-banregio-were-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico City trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IPC index  rose 0.6 percent to 37,271.00.  America Movil  SAB (AMXL MM), the wireless carrier
controlled by billionaire  Carlos Slim , rose 2.2 percent to 16.91
pesos. America Movil, owner of Claro, won the first auction of
the license for 4G technology in Brazil and the license for
wireless frequencies in the country’s rural areas, Brazil’s
telecommunications regulator, known as Anatel, said.  Mexican banks’ outstanding loans rose 0.9 percent to 2.52
trillion pesos ($180 billion) in April from the previous month,
the National Banking and Securities Commission said in an e-
mailed statement yesterday.  Grupo Financiero Banorte SAB (GFNORTEO)  , the only
traditional bank on the benchmark index, climbed 1.9 percent to
62.59 pesos.  Banregio Grupo Financiero SAB (GFREGIO)  , a
Mexican lender focused on loans to small- and medium-sized
businesses, climbed 0.1 percent to 37.35 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
